<dl id="n06155n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06155n">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06155n"> 155(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the commandment with promise / <font color="green">[to pay]</font> <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06155n"><li>FW 62.12 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n06155n">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n06155n">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n06155n">MS BL 47471b-10v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:151 <a name="c20d" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#c20d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c20d.htm#n06155n">Draft: I.3&sect;2.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">FIFTH COMMANDMENT. &ldquo;HONOUR THY FATHER AND THY MOTHER, THAT THY DAYS MAY BE LONG IN THE LAND WHICH THE LORD THY GOD GIVETH THEE.&rdquo; <p>This is called <mark>the commandment with promise</mark>. The blessings promised to those who observe it are, long life, God&apos;s favour, temporal mercies.</p> <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 36</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="n06155f" href="n06all.htm#n06155f">N06 (VI.B.11):155(f)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
